## Summary

Sprint 99 combines two workstreams that landed together in the working tree:

1. **MCP SDK migration** (tracked since the Sonar remediation rounds as a
   deferred `typescript:S1874` item, see `mcp-server-migration-prompt.md`) —
   `src/mcp/server.ts` and `src/mcp/tool-handlers.ts` were modified, and a new
   `src/mcp/schemas.ts` plus a `tests/mcp/` suite were added, consistent with
   the planned move from the deprecated `Server` + `setRequestHandler`
   dispatch pattern to `McpServer` + per-tool `.tool(...)` registration with
   Zod input schemas.
2. **Coverage expansion pass** — a large batch of new/expanded Vitest suites
   landed under `tests/llm/`, `tests/agents/`, `tests/commands/`,
   `tests/memory/`, `tests/policies/`, plus top-level additions
   (`tests/accounts-schema.test.js`, `tests/ai-memory-index.test.js`,
   `tests/browser-selectors-branch-coverage.test.js`,
   `tests/test-runner-branch-gaps.test.js`, `tests/vscode.test.js`), lifting
   coverage substantially over the Sprint 91 baseline (75.35% / 64.16% /
   81.58% stmts/branch/funcs).
3. Generated/derivative artifacts were cleaned from tracking:
   `reports/gitleaks.json`, `sonar-issues.json`, and `sonar_issues.csv` were
   removed from the index, with `sonar-duplicates-by-file.json` and
   `sonar-issues-open.json` left untracked as fresher working exports.
4. `src/llm/_child-process.js` was added, alongside the existing
   `hwProbe.ts`, `security/security-overview/*`, and provider/account files
   carrying forward modifications from adjacent in-flight work.

